Getting Started (Setup Instructions)
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/Philip-bot-bot/mern-app.git
git clone https://github.com/Philip-bot-bot/cypress-mern-app.git

2. Install Dependencies
npm install

3. Start the Backend Server
Run npm install in the root directory
npm run server

4. Start the Frontend App
cd client â†’ npm install
Ensure "react-scripts": "^5.0.1" is in package.json
App runs at http://localhost:3000

5. Run Backend & Frontend Concurrently
npm run dev

âœ… How to Run Tests
UI Tests (Cypress)
npx cypress open
or in headless mode
npx cypress run
Tests cover login, add/edit/delete todos, and form validations.
Custom commands stored in commands.js for cleaner code.

API Tests (Postman + Newman)

Open Postman

Import Mern-app-endpoints.postman_collection.json from the postman folder

Run tests via Postman or Collection Runner

Includes both positive and negative test cases (e.g., login failures, token issues)

Run with Newman (CLI)

Make sure env.json has the token

Run:

bash
Copy
Edit
newman run "Mern-app-endpoints.postman_collection.json" -e "env.json" -r cli,html --reporter-html-export "todo-report.html"
View results in terminal and as an HTML report

